captions.text: -Hey, everyone.

I'm Mindy from Cute
Girls Hair Styles,

and today I'm going to show
you how to do a 3D round braid.

So I have begun already by
just pulling her hair up

into a pony tail and just
to jazz it up a little bit,

I went ahead and did a
French back, you can see.

And I have a video on
how to do this hairstyle

and I will put it right here so
you can click on it if you want

to know how just do
the single French back.

And all I've done
differently is just

teased it before
braiding it today

so it adds a little bit
more fullness on the top,
and I think it looks amazing.

Now, to begin, you're
going to take the pony tail

and just make sure it's
nice and combed out

and then you're going to
section it into four pieces.

So I'm going to just do
one, two, three, and four

and a placed them in
between my four fingers.

Now, if I were going
to number, these hair

strands from left
to right, it would
be one, two, three, and four.

And you're going to
take your pointer finger
and pick up strand number three.

So just reach in there and grab
it, take your middle finger

and pick up strand number
one, and then with these two

strands, you're just going
to twist them and lay

them right in
between your fingers.

So now you have them all in
this hand, in your left hand.

You're going to take
your right hand,

you're going to take
your pointer finger

and pick up strand number
two, reach in there,

and then with your
middle finger,

you're going to pick
up strand number four,

and then these two left
over strands, you're

just going to twist
them again and lay them
in between your fingers.

So right now if
you looked at it,

it kind of looks like
nothing, but ultimately,

when you get the whole braid
done, it looks really cool.

So, again, we're going to
start that whole process over

again, pointer finger, strand
number three, middle finger,

strand number one, and then
flip the last two pieces.

Now, right hand, strand number
two, pick it up, middle finger,

strand number four,
and then flip them.
This is so hard to do slow.
Now, we're going to speed it up.

Three, one, flip the last
two and then two, and four,
flip the last two.

Three, one, flip the last two;
two, four, flip the last two.

Three, one, flip the last two;
two, four, flip the last two.
You see the pattern going?

Three, one, flip the last
two, and I am just about

out of hair, two, four,
and flip the last two.

And then when you get to
where running out of hair,

just secure it with an
elastic that matches the hair
so it's not that visible.

And then you can go
back and pull the edges

a little bit if you want
just to make it look full,
and you're done.
So look at this braid.

If you twist it, it doesn't
matter which way you twist it,

it looks exactly the
same from every angle,
which is why it's like 3D.

Like a normal four-strand
braid would just
lay flat against the head.

In this one, it just is
all round and 3D-looking,

which I love because it's
so cool and different.
And you are finished.
I think it's so adorable.

I know that's one
people comment on

because it's really
different looking.

You just can twist
it all over the place
and it looks exactly the same.

Let's go ahead and spin
you all the way around.

I love the way this
hair style looks.

I think it may be one
of my new favorites.
So fancy, shmancy.

So just for a
little fun today, we

thought we'd get some
viewer interaction

and tell them what
they're going to do.

-So you guys are going to
comment below and tell us

which one of us girls, including
my mom, you are most like.
-Yeah.

So which one of the
CGH girls you think
you're most like and why.

Because we really want to
know how and why you guys

relate to us because we
love all of you guys.

Big hugs from our
family to yours

and we will; see
you guys next week.
Bye.
-Bye.
[MUSIC PLAYING]

(SINGING) You are, you are,
you are every bit of beautiful.

You are, you are, you are
every bit of beautiful.
-Look at this.

As you can see, we're
having a lot of fun.
Wow.

-I can't do it or
I'll fall on my head

because I'm going
to hit the ceiling.
-Nice jump.
-I know.

I was trained not
to land on m laptop.
Leap.
